    <sect3 role="installation">
      <title>Installation of CacheControl</title>

      <para> Build the module: </para>

&build-wheel;

      <para>
        Now, as the <systemitem class="username">root</systemitem> user:
      </para>

<screen role="root"><userinput>&install-wheel; cachecontrol</userinput></screen>

      <para>
        To run the tests, issue:
      </para>

<screen remap="test"><userinput>python3 -m venv --system-site-packages testenv &amp;&amp;
testenv/bin/pip3 install 'cachecontrol[dev]'   &amp;&amp;
testenv/bin/python3 -m pytest</userinput></screen>

      <para>
        pytest may output a warning about an unraisable exception after the
        tests are finished. This is expected due to the version of the 'cheroot'
        module that the tests download.
      </para>

    </sect3>

